    <h1>AN&#xAD;DREA CHONG, 28</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201130/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-30"><time>2020-11-30</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>So­cial me­dia in­flu­encer</p>
    <p>Bet­ter known as Drea Chong and for her col­lab­o­ra­tions with brands such as Ital­ian shoe brand Su­perga, she has gone from run­ning her per­sonal blog to helm­ing fash­ion and life­style web­site The DC Edit with full-time staff last year.</p>
    <p>I was from: Zhonghua Sec­ondary School (2005 to 2006), Vic­to­ria Ju­nior Col­lege (In­te­grated Pro­gramme, 2007 to 2008).</p>
    <p>My best school mem­o­ries:</p>
    <p>“I was a stu­dent coun­cil­lor and very heav­ily in­volved in ex­tracur­ric­u­lar ac­tiv­i­ties. I did drama and de­bate and rep­re­sented my school in golf.”</p>
    <p>One key les­son I’ve learnt: “My teach­ers in­cul­cated in me a sense of dis­ci­pline and a go-get­ting spirit.”</p>
    <p>If I were a stu­dent again: “I’d study harder and sub­mit my home­work on time. I was very in­volved in ex­tracur­ric­u­lar ac­tiv­i­ties and ne­glected my aca­demics a lit­tle in the later years. But I’ve no re­grets now.”</p>

